msgid ""
"Review and edit the server configuration files that control crawling, "
"permalinks and redirects. On subdirectory installs (e.g. /blogbkp2/), Apache"
" may use a root .htaccess in public_html plus a separate one inside "
"WordPress. Also shows all sitemap files detected on this installation."
msgstr ""
"Revisa y edita los archivos de configuración del servidor que controlan el "
"rastreo, los enlaces permanentes y las redirecciones. En instalaciones en "
"subcarpeta (p. ej. /blogbkp2/), Apache puede usar un .htaccess raíz en "
"public_html y otro dentro de WordPress. También muestra los sitemaps "
"detectados."

msgid ".htaccess (domain / document root)"
msgstr ".htaccess (raíz del dominio / document root)"

msgid ".htaccess (WordPress subdirectory)"
msgstr ".htaccess (subcarpeta de WordPress)"

msgid "Document root .htaccess"
msgstr ".htaccess de la raíz del documento"

msgid ""
"This is the .htaccess at your hosting document root (e.g. public_html). It "
"may contain site-wide redirects, security rules or PHP settings that apply "
"before WordPress loads. The WordPress subdirectory has its own .htaccess "
"below for permalinks."
msgstr ""
"Este es el .htaccess en la raíz del hosting (p. ej. public_html). Puede "
"contener redirecciones globales, reglas de seguridad o ajustes PHP que se "
"aplican antes de cargar WordPress. La subcarpeta de WordPress tiene su "
"propio .htaccess abajo para los enlaces permanentes."

msgid "WordPress permalink .htaccess"
msgstr ".htaccess de enlaces permanentes de WordPress"

msgid ""
"This file only affects URLs inside the WordPress folder. Pretty permalinks "
"and rewrite rules for posts/pages are stored here. Site-wide rules in "
"public_html/.htaccess are shown separately above when detected."
msgstr ""
"Este archivo solo afecta a las URLs dentro de la carpeta de WordPress. Aquí "
"están los enlaces permanentes y las reglas de reescritura de "
"entradas/páginas. Las reglas globales de public_html/.htaccess se muestran "
"aparte arriba cuando se detectan."

msgid "Hide WordPress Site Health notices"
msgstr "Ocultar avisos de Salud del sitio de WordPress"

msgid ""
"On staging or private test sites, WordPress may show heavy warnings on Tools"
" › Site Health about search-engine visibility or debug.log being public. "
"Enable the options below to hide those specific tests. This does not change "
"your real settings — it only removes the notices from Site Health."
